The paper introduces a new filtration and theory for stable paths within the filtration, which are inspired by ideas of persistent homology. The paper also applies the filtration and paths to recommendation systems and explainable machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as the paper introduces a new filtration and theory for stable paths. The second most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper applies the filtration and paths to recommendation systems and explainable machine learning. The third most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as the paper discusses the usefulness of the construction in the context of recommendation systems. The fourth most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory) as the paper defines a new filtration based on a generalized Jaccard distance. The fifth most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper applies the filtration and paths to explainable machine learning.
